{
  "texts": [
    "We list simplified estimates of the approximate number of cal-ibrated photon counts (in millions) registered by eROSITA in eRASS1 in the 0.2-2.0 keV band in one hemisphere, split into separate phys-ical components: Cosmic X-ray Background (CXB), Milky Way hot Circum-Galactic Medium (MW hot CGM), Instrumental background (FWC), Local Hot Bubble (LHB), Solar Wind Change Exchange (SWCX), Point Sources (PS), Extended Sources (Ext.",
    "For detailed spectral studies of sources in long pointed observations with high photon statistics further improvements of the RMF and ARF appear to be possible; this work is ongoing at present.",
    "https://erosita.mpe.mpg.de/edr/ Single, double, triple or quadruple events (known as 'patterns') refer to the possible number of pixels within which the charge cloud generated by an X-ray photon can be distributed.",
    "See erosita.mpe.mpg.",
    "de/edr/eROSITATechnical/patternfractions.html for details on how this information can be used to reconstruct the energy and position of the incoming photons."
  ]
}